-- BHP Billiton, Mvelaserve Shares May Move: South African Equities Preview
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s   a n d   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-11-29T06:50:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-28/bhp-billiton-mvelaserve-may-move-south-african-stocks-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  fell 116.84,
or 0.4 percent, to 31,181.38  BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BIL SJ), the world’s biggest mining
company, is seeking a $4 billion credit line to refinance a
facility maturing next year. BHP appointed Barclays Capital as
the coordinator for the five-year revolving credit facility. BHP
fell 1.21 rand, or 0.5 percent, to 256.99 rand.  Gold One International Ltd.  (GDO SJ), the exploration and
mining company, confirmed that output for next year would be
120,000 ounces. Gold One jumped 7 cents, or 2.9 percent, to 2.50
rand.  Massmart Holdings Ltd.  (MSM SJ), South Africa’s biggest
food and general goods wholesaler, said Wal-Mart Stores Inc.
will make an offer to buy 51 percent of the company at 148 rand
per Massmart share. The company’s stock fell 30 cents, or 0.2
percent, to 141.70 rand.  Mvelaserve Ltd.  (MVS SJ), the security and facilities-
management company being spun off from Mvelaphanda Group Ltd.,
starts trading on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange.  Protech Khuthele Holdings Ltd.  (PKH SJ), the South African
civil engineering company, reported first-half headline earnings
per share of 5.9 cents versus 13 cents in the same period a year
earlier. Protech slipped 3 cents, or 4.6 percent, to 63 cents.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc  (AAUKY US) fell 1 percent to $ 22.73.
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd . (AU US) fell 0.9 percent to $46.56.  BHP
Billiton Ltd . (BBL US) declined 1.4 percent to $72.16.  DRDGold
Ltd . (DROOY US) lost 2.9 percent to $4.75.  Gold Fields Ltd . (GFI
US) slid 2.3 percent to $16.46.  Harmony Gold Mining Co . (HMY US)
decreased 3.1 percent to $11.37. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY
US) fell 2.1 percent to $29.15.  Sappi Ltd . (SPP US) slid 1.9
percent to $5.19.  Sasol Ltd . (SSL US) declined 1.6 percent to
$45.97.  The following shares begin trading without the right to
their latest dividend:  Afrimat Ltd. (AFT SJ), Brait SA (BAT SJ), Capitec Bank
Holdings Ltd. (CPI SJ), Coronation Fund Managers Ltd. (CML SJ),
Efficient Finance Holding Ltd. (EFF SJ), Grand Parade
Investments Ltd. (GPL SJ), Investec Plc (INPP SJ), Invicta
Holdings Ltd. (IVT SJ), Mvelaphanda Group Ltd. (MVG SJ), Pan
African Resources Ltd. (PAN SJ), Raubex Group Ltd. (RBX SJ),
SABMiller Plc (SAB SJ), Steinhoff International Holdings Ltd.
(SHF SJ), Vodacom Group Ltd. (VOD SJ), Wooltru Ltd. (WLO SJ).  To contact the reporter on this story:
